1 CHILDREN WHO NEED EMOTIONAL SUPPORT IN A SCHOOL SETTING; AND
2 (II) CERTIFIED OR REGISTERED AS A THERAPY DOG.
3 (B) (1) THERE IS A LIFESAVER SCHOOLS PROGRAM.
4 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO RECOGNIZE PUBLIC
5 SCHOOLS THAT PROVIDE HEALTH AND SAFETY TRAINING TO STUDENTS AND
6 SCHOOL PERSONNEL.
7 (C) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.
8 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DESIGNATE AND PUBLICLY RECOGNIZE
9 A PUBLIC SCHOOL AS A LIFESAVER SCHOOL IF THE SCHOOL APPLIES AND MEETS
10 THE CRITERIA FOR A LIFESAVER SCHOOL ADOPTED BY THE DEPARTMENT IN
11 ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION.
12 (D) (1) AT MINIMUM, THE DEPARTMENT’S CRITERIA FOR A LIFESAVER
13 SCHOOL SHALL REQUIRE A PUBLIC SCHOOL TO:
14 (I) OFFER TO STUDENTS:
15 1. EVIDENCE–BASED TRAINING ON FIRST AID;
16 2. A MENTAL HEALTH WELLNESS PROGRAM OR A PEER
17 MENTORING PROGRAM; AND
18 3. A SCHOOLWIDE ASSEMBLY ON MENTAL HEALTH
19 WELLNESS AND RESOURCES;
20 (II) PROVIDE SERVICE HOURS TO STUDENTS FOR
21 PARTICIPATING IN HEALTH AND SAFETY ACTIVITIES;
22 (III) 1. OFFER TO SCHOOL PERSONNEL AS PROFESSIONAL
23 DEVELOPMENT A MENTAL HEALTH WELLNESS PROGRAM OR TRAINING ON FIRST
24 AID; AND
25 2. AUTHORIZE SCHOOL PERSONNEL TO PARTICIPATE IN
26 THE PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT DURING SCHOOL HOURS, EARN ADDITIONAL
27 COMPENSATION FOR PARTICIPATION, OR RECEIVE CONTINUING EDUCATION
28 CREDITS FOR PARTICIPATION;
29 (IV) ESTABLISH ON THE SCHOOL’S WEBSITE AN EASILY
30 ACCESSIBLE WEBPAGE THAT INCLUDES RESOURCES FOR A MENTAL HEALTH

