1 WELLNESS PROGRAM OR TRAINING ON FIRST AID; AND
2 (V) OFFER TO THE COMMUNITY AN EDUCATIONAL ASSEMBLY
3 ON MENTAL HEALTH WELLNESS AND RESOURCES.
4 (2) A LIFESAVER SCHOOL MAY UTILIZE A CERTIFIED THERAPY DOG
5 PROGRAM IN THE SCHOOL.
6 (E) A PUBLIC SCHOOL MAY PARTNER WITH THE COUNTY BOARD TO FULFILL
7 THE DEPARTMENT’S CRITERIA TO QUALIFY AS A LIFESAVER SCHOOL.
8 (F) ONCE EVERY 4 YEARS, A LIFESAVER SCHOOL IS REQUIRED TO REAPPLY
9 TO THE DEPARTMENT FOR APPROVAL TO MAINTAIN THE LIFESAVER SCHOOL
10 DESIGNATION.
11 (G) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
12 SECTION.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
14 1, 2025.

